  "label": "Sablelink Bunk Alcove",
  "description": "Sablelink Bunk Alcove is a compact sleeping chamber carved from the flat’s slagcrete shell, its surfaces clad in black vitrystone tiles polished dull by abrasive dust. A built-in bunk is set within a recessed niche, with underframe lockers and narrow wall cubbies sized for sealed personal stowage. Layered shutters cover a slit viewport backed by vox-dampening mesh, admitting only a bruise-hued wash from the rift-lit nightside. Overarmored ceiling conduits and heavy gasketed seams emphasize the room’s function as a sealed refuge against ash ingress and electrostatic discharge.",
